21 '2. Members. The commission consists of 18 members as follows:
22 A. Two members of the Senate, including one member of the party holding the largest
23 number of seats in the Legislature and one member of the party holding the 2nd largest
24 number of seats in the Legislature, appointed by the President of the Senate;
25 B. Two members of the House of Representatives, including one member of the party
26 holding the largest number of seats in the Legislature and one member of the party
27 holding the 2nd largest number of seats in the Legislature, appointed by the Speaker of
28 the House of Representatives;
29 C. The director or the director's designee;
30 D. The chair of the board or the chair's designee;
31 E. The following 6 members, appointed by the President of the Senate:
32 (1) A member who represents an organization that is primarily engaged in the
33 provision of nonemergency medical transportation services;
